# Java Core Concepts
A structured repository covering Core Java fundamentals, object-oriented programming, collections, multithreading, Java 8 features, and interview-oriented practice.

## Overview
This repository documents my Java learning journey from fundamentals to advanced Core Java concepts. It contains well-organized examples, practice programs, and implementations that strengthen problem-solving and software development skills.

## Topics Covered
### Java Fundamentals
- Java Introduction
- JVM, JDK, and JRE
- Variables and Data Types
- Operators
- Input and Output
- Conditional Statements
- Loops

### Arrays and Strings
- One-Dimensional Arrays
- Multi-Dimensional Arrays
- String Class
- StringBuilder and StringBuffer

### Methods and OOP
- Methods
- Classes and Objects
- Constructors
- Inheritance
- Polymorphism
- Abstraction
- Encapsulation

### Advanced Core Java
- Wrapper Classes
- Exception Handling
- File Handling
- Collections Framework
- Generics
- Multithreading
- Java 8 Features
  - Lambda Expressions
  - Functional Interfaces
  - Stream API
  - Optional

